-- ArcelorMittal’s Ukrainian Unit Says Steel Output Increased 28%
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-08-16T13:17:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-16/arcelormittal-s-ukrainian-unit-says-steel-output-increased-28-.html
The Ukrainian unit of  ArcelorMittal (MT) ,
the world’s largest steelmaker, increased steel production last
month by 28 percent, the company said without giving a reason.  Steel output rose to 544,100 tons in July compared with
425,100 tons in the same month a year earlier, ArcelorMittal
Kryvyi Rih, based in the city with that name, said in an e-
mailed statement today.  Pig iron production increased to 477,500 tons from 363,900
tons in July last year, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  